content.text:
The issue was that array syntax annotations (e.g., `@[...]`) were not being forced onto separate lines when placed on the same line as the annotated construct. This caused inconsistency with regular annotations which are typically enforced to be on separate lines.

I modified `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/AnnotationRule.kt` to:
1.  Import `KtAnnotation` and `KtAnnotationEntry`.
2.  Add `ANNOTATION` to the list of node types visited by the rule.
3.  Implement `visitAnnotation` to check if an `ANNOTATION` node (array syntax) is on the same line as the annotated construct. If so, it emits a violation and inserts a newline if auto-correct is enabled.
4.  Update `visitAnnotationEntry` to skip `checkForAnnotationWithParameterToBePlacedOnSeparateLine` if the entry is part of an `ANNOTATION` (array syntax), preventing double reporting or conflicting auto-corrections.
5.  Update `getAnnotationUseSiteTarget` to support `KtAnnotation` as well, to correctly identify receiver target annotations which should be skipped.

I verified the changes by creating a new test file `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/AnnotationRuleArraySyntaxTest.kt` with test cases for array annotations on the same line, both with and without parameters. I also ran existing tests in `AnnotationRuleTest.kt` to ensure no regression.

All tests passed.

```kotlin
// ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/AnnotationRule.kt

    override fun beforeVisitChildNodes(
        node: ASTNode,
        autoCorrect: Boolean,
        emit: (offset: Int, errorMessage: String, canBeAutoCorrected: Boolean) -> Unit,
    ) {
        when (node.elementType) {
            FILE_ANNOTATION_LIST -> {
                visitFileAnnotationList(node, emit, autoCorrect)
            }
            ANNOTATION ->
                visitAnnotation(node, emit, autoCorrect)
            ANNOTATION_ENTRY ->
                visitAnnotationEntry(node, emit, autoCorrect)
        }
    }

    private fun visitAnnotation(
        node: ASTNode,
        emit: (offset: Int, errorMessage: String, canBeAutoCorrected: Boolean) -> Unit,
        autoCorrect: Boolean,
    ) {
        if (node.treeParent.elementType == FILE_ANNOTATION_LIST ||
            node.treeParent.treeParent.elementType == VALUE_PARAMETER ||
            node.treeParent.treeParent.elementType == VALUE_ARGUMENT ||
            node.isPartOf(TYPE_ARGUMENT_LIST) ||
            !node.isNotReceiverTargetAnnotation()
        ) {
            return
        }

        if (node.isOnSameLineAsAnnotatedConstruct()) {
            emit(
                node.startOffset,
                "Annotation must be placed on separate line",
                true,
            )
            if (autoCorrect) {
                node
                    .lastChildLeafOrSelf()
                    .nextLeaf()
                    ?.upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe(getNewlineWithIndent(node.treeParent))
            }
        }
    }
